## Recurring date filter

This is an advanced date filter, suitable for event search. It uses as a source a [Recurring date](docs.getvoxel.io_articles_recurring-date-field_.md) field

## Options

- Label
- Description
- Key
- Data source: Requires a Recurring date field as source
- Input mode: Single date or Date range
- Match ongoing dates
- From label: If Date range mode
- To label: If Date range mode
- Placeholder: If Single date mode
- Description
- Icon

## Input modes

A preview of Single date input mode

![](data:image/png;base64,)

A preview of Date range input mode

![](data:image/png;base64,)

When filter input mode is set to Date Range, you can also enable some presets when configuring the filter on the Search form widget. These include:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- All
- Upcoming
- Today
- Tomorrow
- This weekend
- This week
- Next week
- Next 7 days
- This month
- Next month
- Next 30 days
- This year
- Next year
- Next 365 days

## Default values

As default value for this filter, you an apply presets above, or choose custom date or date range.

For example, if you want to hide past dates from search results, you can set default value to Upcoming preset.
